decision_conditions: The development permitted shall be begun before the expiration of three years from the date of the original permission.

REASON: In order to comply with the provisions of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990 (as amended). | The external elevations of the perimeter fencing shall be finished with green paint, unless otherwise agreed in writing by the Local Planning Authority.

REASON:  To ensure that the fencing harmonises with the surroundings, in accordance with policies D3, D4 and G3 of the London Plan (2021) and policies 5.10, 7.4 and 7B of the Ealing Development Management DPD (2013). | Notwithstanding the information shown on the submitted plans details of soft landscaping works, including a phased programme of works must be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. Soft landscaping works shall be carried out in accordance with the approved details prior to the first use of the development, and permanently retained, unless otherwise agreed in writing with the Local Planning Authority.

REASON:  To ensure that the development is landscaped in the interests of the visual character and appearance of the area in accordance with D3, D4, G3 and G7 of the London Plan (2021) and policies 5.10, 7.4 and 7B of the Ealing Development Management DPD (2013). | The existing trees on the site shall not be lopped, felled or otherwise affected in any way (including raising or lowering soil levels under the crown spread of the trees) and no excavation shall be cut under the crown spread of the trees without the prior written permission of the Local Planning Authority.

REASON:  To safeguard the trees in the interest of visual character and appearance of the area in accordance with policies D3, D4, G3 and G7 of the London Plan (2021), policies 5.10, 7.4 and 7B of the Ealing Development Management DPD (2013) and Supplementary Planning Document 9. | The area beneath the spread of the branches of the trees as shown on the approved drawings shall not be used for the storage of building materials, plant, machinery or other items, or for vehicular access or for the burning of materials of any kind.

REASON:  To prevent damage to the trees in the interest of the visual character and appearance of the area in accordance with policies D3, D4, G3 and G7 of the London Plan (2021), policies 5.10, 7.4 and 7B of the Ealing Development Management DPD (2013) and Supplementary Planning Document 9. | No external lighting (floodlighting) shall be installed on or adjacent to the site without prior approval of the Local Planning Authority, obtained through the submission of a separate planning application.

REASON:  To protect the character of the land, and the amenity of nearby residents in accordance with the policies 7.4, 7A and 7B of the Ealing Development Management DPD (2013). | The use of the artificial sports pitch and cricket nets hereby permitted shall only occur between Monday - Sunday 09:00-21:30 and the use of the pavilion shall only occur between Monday-Sunday 08:00-22:00, and at no other times unless otherwise agreed in writing by the local planning authority.

REASON: In the interests of the living conditions of occupiers of nearby properties, in accordance with policy D6 of the London Plan (2021) and Policies 7.4, 7A and 7B of the Ealing Development Management DPD (2013). | The topographic survey of ground levels above Ordnance Datum, contoured at 0.2m intervals, as a result of the compensatory works shall be carried out in accordance with the details previously approved under ref: P/2010/2362 dated 30/09/2010.

REASON: To ensure the development is subject to the minimum risk of flooding in accordance with policies SI12 and SI13 of the London Plan (2021) and Supplementary Planning Guidance 2 (Water, drainage and flooding). | There shall be no storage of materials including soil within that part of the site liable to flood.

REASON: To prevent the increased risk of flooding due to impedance of flood flows and reduction of flood storage capacity in accordance with policy SI12 and SI13 of the London Plan (2021) and Supplementary Planning Guidance 2 (Water, drainage and flooding). | Compensatory flood storage works shall only be carried out in accordance with the approved technical note WN/JMIS/057/D5036 Rev 3 (Halcrow Group March 2010).

REASON: To alleviate the increased risk of flooding that would otherwise be caused by a reduction in flood storage capacity in accordance with policies SI12 and SI13 of the London Plan (2021) and Supplementary Planning Guidance 2 (Water, drainage and flooding). | The details of a tree protection method statement shall be carried out in accordance with the details previously approved under ref: P/2010/2568 dated 18.10.2010.

REASON: To prevent damage to the protected trees in the interest of the visual character and appearance of the area in accordance with adopted policy 2.18 of the Ealing Development Management DPD (2013) and Policy G7 of the London Plan (2021). | For the duration of the site preparation, construction and finishing out and until the proposed site is occupied, no deliveries to the site shall take place before 09:30 and after 16:00 Monday to Friday, before 09:30 and after 13:00 on Saturdays, and not at all on Sundays or public and bank holidays.

REASON: To ensure highway safety and to protect the living conditions of neighbouring occupiers in accordance with policies 6.13 and 7B of the Ealing Development Management DPD (2013). | The proposed artificial sports pitch and cricket nets shall be designed to be permeable to water including flood water.

REASON: To prevent obstruction to the flow and storage of floodwater, with a consequent increased risk of flooding in accordance with policies SI12 and SI13 of the London Plan (2013) and Supplementary Planning Guidance 2 (Water, drainage and flooding). | The details of an alternative location for the northern spectator area (not adjacent to the northern site boundary) shall be carried out in accordance with the details previously approved under ref: PP/2010/2569 dated 23.08.2010.

REASON: To protect the living conditions of neighbouring occupiers in accordance with policies 7A and 7B of the Ealing Development Management DPD (2013). | A revised Green Travel Plan, designed to manage the transport needs of residents and visitors to minimise car usage and promote alternative modes of transport, shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The approved Green Travel Plan shall be implemented on first use of the development hereby permitted, and shall be retained in operation thereafter, unless otherwise agreed in writing by the Local Planning Authority. Thereafter, an annual monitoring report shall be submitted to the Local Planning Authority, unless otherwise requested.

REASON: To promote sustainable patterns of transport, to safeguard the living and working conditions of local people and in the interests of highway and pedestrian safety, in accordance with policy 6.13 and 7B od the Ealing Development Management DPD (2013). | The development shall operate in accordance with the vehicular access and parking management arrangements contained within appendix 3 of the submitted additional transport information.
REASON: In the interests of highway safety and to protect the living conditions of neighbouring occupiers in accordance with policies 6.13 and 7B of the Ealing Development Management DPD (2013).
description: Application for a Minor Material Amendment (S73a) to vary condition 7 (Operating Hours) of planning permission ref: PP/2010/1355 dated: 02/06/2010 for: Construction of artificial sports pitch with fencing and spectator area; and the replacement of part of the existing multi-use games area (MUGA) with 2-lane cricket nets. Amendment seeks changes to operating hours of Sports Field Pitches and Courts restricted by condition 7.
